Lands/Conquered</span><hr size=1> The Country of the Warrior women,The Amazons-The daughters,Strangey enough of that most peace-loveing Nymph,sweet Harmony.But their fater was Ares,The terrable god of war,whose ways of war they followed and not their mother's.The heroes would gladly have halted and closed battle with them,.and it would not have been a battle without bloodshed.for the Amazons were not gentle foes.<br>But the wind was favorable and they hurried on. they caught glimpse of the Caucasus as they sped past,and of Prometheus on his rock high above them,and they heard the fanning of the eagle's huge wings as it darted down to its bloody feast.they stopped for nothing ,and,and that same day at sunset they reached Colchis,the country of the Golden Fleece. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ucallistoblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CallistoBlade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#993300>(12/16/00 11:24:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hippolyta</span><hr size=1> Theseus whent to the Country of the Amazon's,the women Warriors,some say with Hercules,some say alone. and brought away one of them,whose name is given sometimes as Antiope,sometimes as Hippolyta.It is certian that the son she bore Theseys was named Hippolyttus, and also that after his birth the Amazons came to Rescue her and Invaded Attica,the country around Athens,even making their way into the city. They were finally defeated and no other enemy entered Attica as long as Theseus lived.<br><br>((That SUCKS!)) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=11.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href=